"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1934092-Olympic-Games-Abebe-Bikila-marathon-running-athletics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Running shoes are as important as endurance when it comes to running a marathon - unless you are two-time Olympic gold medallist Abebe Bikila.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 131, \"end\": 143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abebe_Bikila\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Abebe Bikila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abebe_Bikila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abebe_Bikila\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The legendary long-distance runner is one of the most unique competitors to ever appear at theOlympic Games.\", \"from\": 145, \"to\": 253, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Ethiopian's unconventional approach to competition and his journey to the 1960 Rome Olympics were anything but ordinary.\", \"from\": 255, \"to\": 379, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 259, \"end\": 268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9990713433216265, \"rank\": 0.0009294935122439238, \"text\": \"Ethiopian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bikila, who died at the age of 41 from a cerebral haemorrhage in 1973, was not initially chosen to compete in the Italian games.\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 494, \"end\": 501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.5895403470560532, \"rank\": 0.690564965318252, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He only got the opportunity because his team-mate Wami Biratu sustained an injury while playing football.\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 615, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite these circumstances, he went on to win gold in extraordinary fashion - all without wearing any shoes.\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 725, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bikila's athletic career started when he was serving as a bodyguard for the Ethiopian Royal Family.\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 826, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 803, \"end\": 812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9990713433216265, \"rank\": 0.0009294935122439238, \"text\": \"Ethiopian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 813, \"end\": 825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_royal_family\", \"score\": 0.944424527635758, \"rank\": 0.058725925026927, \"text\": \"Royal Family\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_royal_family\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_royal_family\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His potential was noticed during his training sessions.\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He first caught the attention of coaches with his habit of running barefoot.\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 959, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After his unexpected selection for the Olympics, the initial task was to find him a suitable pair of trainers.\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 1071, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This proved to be arduous as they could not find any which were the right size and did not leave him with agonising blisters.\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1197, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bikila stuck to what he was comfortable with - his bare, unprotected feet running 26.2 miles across concrete, stones and whoever knows what else.\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1344, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The unusual practice of running barefoot brought extra attention and pressure, but Bikila remained unfazed.\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1452, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His focus was solely on the gold medal and his main competitor, Moroccan Rhadi Ben Abdesselam, whom his coach had warned him about.\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1584, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1517, \"end\": 1525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 0.9999999957408363, \"rank\": 2.617048240675516e-09, \"text\": \"Moroccan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}, {\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhadi_Ben_Abdesselam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rhadi Ben Abdesselam\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhadi_Ben_Abdesselam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhadi_Ben_Abdesselam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bikila's coach told him to look out for No.\", \"from\": 1586, \"to\": 1629, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"26, but a mix-up with the numbers saw Rhadi wear No.185 instead, causing him to frantically search for the Moroccan when he was by his side for the majority of the race.\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1737, \"end\": 1745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 0.9999999957408363, \"rank\": 2.617048240675516e-09, \"text\": \"Moroccan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Interestingly, the race started in the late afternoon and ended at night.\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1873, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Under the starlit sky, it was Bikila who shone the brightest.\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1938, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the final 500m, it seemed like a close contest between Rhadi and Bikila, but the Ethiopian found an extra gear and sprinted to the finish line, winning by 25 seconds and setting a new world record.\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 2139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2023, \"end\": 2032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9990713433216265, \"rank\": 0.0009294935122439238, \"text\": \"Ethiopian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you.\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2250, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding.\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2327, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time.\", \"from\": 2328, \"to\": 2360, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy Policy  His victory marked the first time an athlete from sub-Saharan Africa had won an Olympic gold medal, paving the way for a golden era of African long-distance runners.\", \"from\": 2361, \"to\": 2550, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Four years later, Bikila finally found a pair of Puma trainers that were comfortable and did not cause blisters.\", \"from\": 2551, \"to\": 2663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just weeks before the Tokyo Olympics in 1964, he was diagnosed with acute appendicitis and had to undergo surgery.\", \"from\": 2665, \"to\": 2779, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He managed to build such a commanding lead that he entered the 75,000-capacity stadium alone for the final stretch, crossing the finish line a staggering four minutes and eight seconds ahead of Great Britain's silver medallist, Basil Heatley.\", \"from\": 2780, \"to\": 3022, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2974, \"end\": 2987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9922811623648186, \"rank\": 0.007778493637052859, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 3008, \"end\": 3021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basil_Heatley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Basil Heatley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basil_Heatley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basil_Heatley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To further sum up how super human he was, Bikila even celebrated by performing a calisthenics routine for the adoring crowd.\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3147, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.\", \"from\": 3149, \"to\": 3318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3286, \"end\": 3299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.789982632328095e-18, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\", \"from\": 3320, \"to\": 3387, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3335, \"end\": 3348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.789982632328095e-18, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}]}"